# THE ALOA — Phase 1: System Control Foundation

**A Python-based Autonomous Laptop Operating Agent** that gives users OS-level control over software lifecycle management and system health diagnostics via a rich interactive CLI.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Technology Choice**: Python 3.10+ with `psutil`, `winreg`, and `rich` for the CLI. This gives us deep OS integration while keeping the codebase maintainable. Please confirm you have Python 3.10+ installed.

> [!WARNING]
> **Elevated Privileges**: Many operations (registry access, service removal, PATH modification) require **Administrator** privileges. The agent will detect and warn when elevation is needed.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Deep Uninstall** removes binaries, caches, configs, and services. The agent will always show a preview and require confirmation before destructive operations.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph CLI["Interactive CLI (Rich)"]
        REPL["REPL Loop"]
        PARSER["Command Parser"]
    end

    subgraph CORE["Core Agent"]
        REGISTRY["Module Registry"]
        EXECUTOR["Command Executor"]
        PRIV["Privilege Manager"]
    end

    subgraph ALM["App Lifecycle Manager"]
        INSTALL["Installer (winget / flags)"]
        PATH_CFG["PATH Configurator"]
        REG_DETECT["Registry Detector"]
        UNINSTALL["Deep Uninstaller"]
        VERIFY["Verification Engine"]
    end

    subgraph SHPE["System Health Engine"]
        RAM["RAM Monitor"]
        CPU["CPU Analyzer"]
        DISK["Disk Inspector"]
        STARTUP["Startup Analyzer"]
        UNUSED["Unused App Detector"]
        BOTTLENECK["Bottleneck Finder"]
        SUGGEST["Suggestion Engine"]
    end

    REPL --> PARSER --> REGISTRY
    REGISTRY --> EXECUTOR
    EXECUTOR --> PRIV
    EXECUTOR --> ALM
    EXECUTOR --> SHPE
```

