## Proposed Changes

### Core Framework

#### [NEW] [main.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/main.py)
- Rich REPL loop with banner, prompt, and help system
- Routes user input to the agent orchestrator
- Graceful error handling and exit

#### [NEW] [agent.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/core/agent.py)
- Module registry: maps command keywords → handler functions
- Central `execute(command)` method that parses and dispatches

#### [NEW] [parser.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/core/parser.py)
- Keyword-based command parser
- Supports natural-language-like inputs: `"install maven"`, `"why is my laptop slow?"`
- Extracts intent (install / uninstall / health / diagnose) and target

#### [NEW] [privileges.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/core/privileges.py)
- Detect if running as admin via `ctypes.windll.shell32`
- Warn user when elevation is required
- Helper to re-launch as admin if needed

---

### Intelligent Application Lifecycle Manager

#### [NEW] [installer.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/lifecycle/installer.py)
- **`winget install`** with `--silent --accept-package-agreements` flags
- Fallback: direct installer download + silent flags (`/S`, `/VERYSILENT`, etc.)
- Progress tracking via Rich progress bar
- Post-install PATH update trigger

#### [NEW] [path_config.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/lifecycle/path_config.py)
- Read/write `HKCU\Environment\Path` (user-level) and `HKLM\...\Environment\Path` (system-level)
- Auto-detect common bin directories (e.g., `\bin`, `\Scripts`)
- Broadcast `WM_SETTINGCHANGE` to refresh environment without restart

#### [NEW] [registry.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/lifecycle/registry.py)
- Scan `HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Uninstall` and WOW6432Node
- Extract: install location, display name, version, publisher, uninstall string
- Build a searchable app catalog

#### [NEW] [uninstaller.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/lifecycle/uninstaller.py)
- Run native uninstaller from registry `UninstallString`
- Deep cleanup:
  - Remove install directory
  - Remove `%APPDATA%`, `%LOCALAPPDATA%` app folders
  - Remove `%TEMP%` remnants
  - Stop and remove related Windows services (`sc stop`, `sc delete`)
- Preview mode: show what **would** be removed before acting

#### [NEW] [verifier.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/lifecycle/verifier.py)
- Check if executable is on PATH (`shutil.which`)
- Run `<app> --version` to confirm working installation
- Verify registry entry exists
- Report: ✅ installed, on PATH, version X.Y.Z

---

### Autonomous System Health & Performance Engine

#### [NEW] [ram_monitor.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/ram_monitor.py)
- `psutil.virtual_memory()` for total/used/available/percent
- Top N processes by memory consumption
- Flag processes using > threshold% of RAM

#### [NEW] [cpu_monitor.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/cpu_monitor.py)
- `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1, percpu=True)` for per-core load
- Detect sustained spikes (> 80% for > 5s)
- Top N processes by CPU usage

#### [NEW] [disk_inspector.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/disk_inspector.py)
- Per-drive usage via `psutil.disk_usage()`
- Clutter scan: `%TEMP%`, browser caches, Windows update cache, Recycle Bin size
- Large file finder (files > configurable threshold)

#### [NEW] [startup_analyzer.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/startup_analyzer.py)
- Read startup entries from:
  - Registry `Run` keys (HKCU + HKLM)
  - `shell:startup` folder
  - Scheduled tasks (`schtasks /query`)
- Estimate impact: high / medium / low based on resource usage

#### [NEW] [unused_apps.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/unused_apps.py)
- Cross-reference installed apps (from registry) with recent usage
- Check file last-access timestamps on executables
- Flag apps not launched in > 90 days

#### [NEW] [bottleneck.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/bottleneck.py)
- Composite analysis: RAM pressure + CPU load + disk I/O + swap usage
- Identify the primary bottleneck category
- Clear English explanation: "Your laptop is slow because RAM is at 94%, Chrome is using 3.2 GB"

#### [NEW] [suggestions.py](file:///e:/miniproject/aloa/health/suggestions.py)
- Generate ranked suggestions based on bottleneck analysis
- Actionable items: "Kill Chrome (save 3.2 GB RAM)", "Disable Spotify from startup"
- Optional execution: user can approve suggestions to be executed immediately

---

